# React UI patterns

## Reference component
- `src/components/school/SchoolDashboard.jsx` is the gold standard. Match its structure, spacing, and polish.

## Form helpers
Reuse `FormInput` and `FormSelect` from `SchoolDashboard.jsx` when building forms. If used in more than two places, extract to `src/components/ui/form-helpers.jsx`.

## Typical page structure
```jsx
<div className="space-y-6">
  <div className="flex items-center justify-between">
    <div>
      <h1 className="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800">Title</h1>
      <p className="text-slate-500 text-sm mt-1">Subtitle</p>
    </div>
    {/* optional action button */}
  </div>

  {/* stat cards grid */}
  <div className="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-4 gap-4">...</div>

  {/* main content in white cards */}
  <div className="bg-white rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm border border-gray-100">...</div>
</div>
```

## Empty states
Every list must have an empty state:
```jsx
{items.length === 0 ? (
  <div className="text-center py-16 text-slate-400">
    <Icon className="w-12 h-12 mx-auto mb-3 opacity-30" />
    <p className="text-sm">No <things> yet.</p>
  </div>
) : ( /* actual list */ )}
```

## Loading states
Use existing `Skeleton` from `src/components/ui/skeleton.jsx` — never a bare "Loading..." string inside cards.

## Color semantics
| Intent | Tailwind |
|--------|----------|
| Primary action | `bg-indigo-600 hover:bg-indigo-700 text-white` |
| Success | `bg-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-700 text-white` |
| Warning | `bg-amber-500 hover:bg-amber-600 text-white` |
| Danger | `bg-red-500 hover:bg-red-600 text-white` |
| Secondary | `bg-slate-100 hover:bg-slate-200 text-slate-700` |

## Icons
- From `lucide-react`, size `w-4 h-4` default, `w-5 h-5` for header icons.
- When passing Icon as a prop, render with `createElement(Icon, { className })`.

## Role-specific UX
- Admin/School → data tables, dialogs for CRUD
- Teacher → workflow-oriented, one clear next action per screen
- Student → friendly, celebratory where possible (grades, achievements)

## Accessibility
- All buttons need `type="button"` unless submitting a form.
- Inputs need associated `<label>`.
- Never rely on color alone to convey state — add an icon or text.
